<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Bequeath" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Bequeath,</orth> to leave by will: <bibl n="shak. luc 534" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 534</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 534" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 534</bibl> <bibl n="shak. luc 534" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 534</bibl> <bibl n="shak. pp 142" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 142</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 1, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 1.1.44" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 1, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 1.3.105" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 105</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 4.2.43" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 43</bibl> <cit><quote>(--ed down from many ancestors).</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 1.109" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 109</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.149" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 2, 149</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.10.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 10, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.2.141" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 2, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.1.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 1, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.1.130" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 130</bibl>.<lb />2) in a wider sense, == to leave, to yield, to bestow upon: <cit><quote>her contrite sighs unto the clouds --ed her winged sprite,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1727" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1727</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>my horns I b. your husbands,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.30" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 5, 30</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>and yours of Helena to me b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.166" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 166</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>his crown --ing to his banished brother,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.4.169" default="NO" valid="yes">As V, 4, 169</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>you to your former honour I b.,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.4.169" default="NO" valid="yes">As V, 4, 169</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>b. to death your numbness,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 5.3.102" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 3, 102</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>b. thy land to him and follow me,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 1.149" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 149</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to whom I do b. my faithful services,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 5.7.104" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 7, 104</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a sister I b. you,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 2.2.152" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 2, 152</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>